Line $l$ is a straight line. What is the value of $x$ in the diagram? [asy]

size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8)); import geometry;

draw(origin--(10,0),Arrows);

pair X = (5,0) + 5*dir(74);

draw((5,0)--X,EndArrow);

label("$x + 26^\circ$",(5,0),NE);

label("$2x+10^\circ$",(5,0),NW);

label("$l$",(0,0),NW);

[/asy]

answer_cot:
We have  \begin{align*}
\frac{12}{x \cdot x} \cdot \frac{x^4}{14x}\cdot \frac{35}{3x} &=
\frac{12 \cdot x^4 \cdot 35}{x^2\cdot 14x \cdot 3x}\\& = \frac{(4 \cdot 3) \cdot (5 \cdot 7) \cdot x^4}{(3 \cdot 2 \cdot 7)(x^2 \cdot x \cdot x)}\\
&= \frac{2\cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot 7}{2 \cdot 3 \cdot 7}\cdot\frac{x^4}{x^{4}}\\
&= 2 \cdot 5 = \boxed{10}.
\end{align*}

Since $\mathbf{a}, \mathbf{b},$ and $\mathbf{a-b}$ all lie in the same plane, from the diagram below, we see that the angle between $\mathbf{a}$ and $\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b}$ is $84^\circ - 29^\circ = \boxed{55^\circ}.$

[asy]
unitsize(5 cm);

pair A, B, C, O;

O = (0,0);
A = (1,0);
B = extension(O, O + dir(29), A, A + dir(180 - 55));
C = O + A - B;

draw(O--A,red,Arrow(6));
draw(O--B,green,Arrow(6));
draw(C--A,green,Arrow(6));
draw(O--C,blue,Arrow(6));
draw(B--A,blue,Arrow(6));

label("$\mathbf{a}$", A/2, S);
label("$\mathbf{b}$", B/2, NW);
